            "id": "4540259",
            "title": "OpenAI CFO says ARR hits above $20B in 2025",
            "description": "<html><body><p data-eci=\"true\"><span>OpenAI's (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/OPENAI\" title=\"OpenAI\">OPENAI</a>) CFO, Sarah Friar, said that the company's annualized revenue surpassed $20B in 2025, more than tripling from $6B in 2024 and <span>up from $2B in 2023.</span></span></p>\n<p><span><span>Friar also pointed to massive expansion in computing capacity from 0.6 gigawatts in 2024 to 1.9 gigawatts in 2025, fueling unprecedented daily and weekly active users.</span></span></p>\n<p><span><span>\"Both our Weekly Active User (WAU) and Daily Active User (DAU) figures continue to produce all-time highs. This growth is driven by a flywheel across compute, frontier research, products, and monetization. Investment in compute powers leading-edge research and step-change gains in model capability. Stronger models unlock better products and broader adoption of the OpenAI platform. Adoption drives revenue, and revenue funds the next wave of compute and innovation. The cycle compounds,\" <a href=\"https://openai.com/index/a-business-that-scales-with-the-value-of-intelligence/?utm_source=chatgpt.com\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"commented\">commented</a> Friar.</span></span></p>\n<p><span><span>The research lab behind ChatGPT said that it maintains a lean balance sheet through flexible partnerships rather than owning infrastructure.</span></span></p>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"signup_widget_placeholder\"></div>\n</body></html>",
            "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/assets/og_image_1200-29b2bfe1a595477db6826bd2126c63ac2091efb7ec76347a8e7f81ba17e3de6c.png",
